The paper proposes a new data structure for efficient intersection and union operations on document identifiers, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) systems. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions that the group-list is as simple as the inverted index, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper mentions experimental results on a synthetic dataset, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DL (Machine Learning) or cs.LG (Machine Learning and Statistics).
